cs.CR, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.MM

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category as it deals with technical support scams and their abuse tactics. It may also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as the authors use a data-driven approach to understand search-and-ad abuse by TSS. Additionally, it may belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as the scammers use social engineering over the phone channel. It could also belong to cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it deals with online abuse and its impact on society. Finally, it may belong to cs.MM (Multimedia) as the scammers use multimedia elements such as advertisements to lure victims.
